      188.97
    ],
    "text": "R. Gurusinghe, J.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      217.09,
      542.91,
      230.37
    ],
    "text": "The Accused-Appellant (Appellant) was indicted in the High Court of Trincomalee for",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      235.86,
      542.89,
      251.13
    ],
    "text": "committing the murder of Nadarasa Sudharan on 22nd of July 2006, an offence punishable under",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      8.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      258.52,
      543.06,
      271.8
    ],
    "text": "Section 296 of the Penal Code. After trial the learned High Court Judge convicted the Appellant",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      279.28,
      260.57,
      292.56
    ],
    "text": "for the offence and sentenced to death.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      318.69,
      543.0,
      333.96
    ],
    "text": "The Appellant appealed against the said Judgment and sentence dated 23rd July 2015 on the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      8.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      341.32,
      221.69,
      354.6
    ],
    "text": "grounds set out in the appeal.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      382.72,
      542.95,
      396.0
    ],
    "text": "The Appellants position right throughout the trial was that the deceased tried to grab hold of the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      403.48,
      542.93,
      416.76
    ],
    "text": "gun that was in possession of the accused. The Accused-Appellant was serving as a home guard",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      424.14,
      542.96,
      437.42
    ],
    "text": "officer at a building called APC building which was located in Kachchakoditeeve an area which",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      444.9,
      543.1,
      458.18
    ],
    "text": "was a war zone during the year 2006. The duty of the Appellant was to give security to the APC",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      465.54,
      528.22,
      478.82
    ],
    "text": "and the nearby camp. This was the time that war between Army and the LTTE was at its peak.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman",
      "Times New Roman,Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      504.95,
      542.93,
      520.22
    ],
    "text": "The incident happened on 22nd July 2006 around 11.30 a.m. Appellant came out to the road to",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      8.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      527.7,
      543.08,
      540.98
    ],
    "text": "see if the vehicle carrying lunch for the soldiers was coming. At that time, he noticed a man (the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      548.34,
      543.02,
      561.62
    ],
    "text": "deceased) on a racing bicycle roaming around in that area. He noticed the deceased three times.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      569.1,
      543.08,
      582.38
    ],
    "text": "The Appellants position is that all of a sudden, the deceased came towards the Appellant and",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      589.77,
      543.06,
      603.05
    ],
    "text": "attempted to grab hold of the gun; the Appellant cried out for help shouting Corporal,",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      610.53,
      542.74,
      623.81
    ],
    "text": "Corporal. However, before the Corporal came for help the Appellant pushed the deceased and",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman",
      "Times New Roman,Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      631.17,
      543.06,
      644.45
    ],
    "text": "the deceased fell on the ground and then the deceased put his hand into the pocket of his shorts",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      651.93,
      542.89,
      665.21
    ],
    "text": "that he was wearing inside the sarong. At that moment, the Appellant realised that he was taking",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      672.57,
      543.06,
      685.85
    ],
    "text": "out a hand grenade or a pistol and as the Appellant has to act very quickly, he had no option but",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      693.32,
      398.23,
      706.61
    ],
    "text": "to fire the deceased. He fired a shot and ran into the APC building.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      731.86,
      311.31,
      756.34
    ],
    "text": "3",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      72.25,
      543.1,
      85.53
    ],
    "text": "Prosecution has called the following witnesses and produced the T 56 gun and the post-mortem",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      92.89,
      542.96,
      106.17
    ],
    "text": "report of the deceased. The prosecution called PW2 T.K.D.S.Gamini Army Corporal who was in",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      113.65,
      542.8,
      126.93
    ],
    "text": "charge of the place, PW10 M.A.N. Jakath, Pw19 the doctor, P1W17 the Inspector of Police,",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      134.29,
      263.09,
      147.57
    ],
    "text": "PW1 S.M. Nawas and PW5 S. Mekala.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      175.69,
      543.08,
      188.97
    ],
    "text": "PW2 has given evidence to the effect that he was in charge of an army sentry point that was",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      196.45,
      542.99,
      209.73
    ],
    "text": "located in the APC building of Kachchakoditeeve to provide security. The Appellant was doing",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      217.09,
      542.96,
      230.37
    ],
    "text": "his duty as a home guard under witness No. 2 on the day of the incident. PW2 heard the shout",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      237.85,
      542.89,
      251.13
    ],
    "text": "Corporal, Corporal and immediately he heard a gun fire. PW2 rushed to the scene and",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman",
      "Times New Roman,Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      258.52,
      543.09,
      271.8
    ],
    "text": "inquired from the Appellant as to what had happened. Then the Appellant told him that the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      279.28,
      542.89,
      292.56
    ],
    "text": "deceased had attempted to grab hold of the gun and scuffled and fell. This witness also admitted",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      299.92,
      543.01,
      313.2
    ],
    "text": "that there were LTTE activities present during the time of the incident. He further said that",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      320.68,
      543.1,
      333.96
    ],
    "text": "neighbouring area was occupied by the LTTE. Witness No. 2 then informed the police and the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      341.32,
      543.08,
      354.6
    ],
    "text": "police came there. When the police tried to lift the body of the deceased, they found a grenade.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      362.08,
      543.1,
      375.36
    ],
    "text": "PW2 said police had asked him to take the grenade and then PW2 had taken it from the pocket of",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      382.72,
      543.1,
      396.0
    ],
    "text": "the shorts of the deceased. He said that it was a live grenade. The police witness said that the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      403.48,
      362.35,
      416.76
    ],
    "text": "grenade was detonated later on the orders of the Magistrate.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      444.9,
      543.1,
      458.18
    ],
    "text": "The deceased was not a known person to the accused. After the prosecution case is closed, the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
